    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces, then add to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender, then drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomato-and-pulled-chicken-breast-potato-topped-pie/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are boiling, reboil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Top, tail, peel and dice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomato-and-pulled-chicken-breast-potato-topped-pie/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> chopped</strong> <strong>onion </strong>and <strong>carrot </strong>and cook for 3 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Meanwhile dissolve your <strong>beef stock mix</strong>, <strong>tomato paste </strong>and <strong>Marmite</strong> in 250ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [425ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>and stir in your <strong>soy sauce </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>rich tomato stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomato-and-pulled-chicken-breast-potato-topped-pie/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the vegetables have softened, turn the heat up to high, then add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and your <strong>chicken breast portion[s] </strong>and cook for 3 min on each side or until browned</p><p>Once browned, reduce the head to medium-high, then add your <strong>red wine vinegar </strong>and cook for 1 min further or until reduced slightly</p><p>Add the <strong>rich tomato stock </strong>and <strong>bay leaf[ves]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>and cook, covered, for a further 10-12 min or until the sauce has thickened and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomato-and-pulled-chicken-breast-potato-topped-pie/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, return the<strong> drained potatoes</strong> to a low heat with a generous knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a splash of <strong>milk</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and mash until smooth \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy mash</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomato-and-pulled-chicken-breast-potato-topped-pie/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is cooked, transfer it to a clean board and shred it apart using two forks \u2013 this technique is known as 'pulling'</p><p>Remove your <strong>bay leaf[ves]</strong> from the pan</p><p>Return the <strong>pulled chicken </strong>to the pan with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your<strong> pulled chicken pie filling</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomato-and-pulled-chicken-breast-potato-topped-pie/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>pulled chicken pie filling</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish </strong>and top evenly with the <strong>creamy mash</strong></p><p>Put the dish in the oven for 12-15 min or until golden and bubbling \u2013 this is your<strong> tomato & pulled chicken breast potato-topped pie</strong></p><p>Reboil half a kettle</p><p>Once the pie is nearly ready, add your <strong>blanched peas </strong>to a colander and pour plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>all over them until they're warmed through</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomato-and-pulled-chicken-breast-potato-topped-pie/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>tomato & pulled chicken breast potato-topped pie </strong>with the <strong>warmed peas</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
